# 🚇 TransitFlow - Multi-Modal Urban Transit Integration Platform

> **Transforming urban commuting by treating travel as a single, continuous journey instead of disconnected transport segments.**

[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-blue.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Node.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Node.js-16%2B-green.svg)](https://nodejs.org/)
[![React](https://img.shields.io/badge/React-18.2-blue.svg)](https://reactjs.org/)

---

## 🎯 What is TransitFlow?

TransitFlow is a **complete urban transit platform** that solves the fragmented commuting experience by:

- 🗺️ **Unifying all transport modes** (trains, metro, buses, autos, walking) into single routes
- ⚡ **Providing real-time updates** on delays, crowds, and disruptions
- 🔄 **Offering instant alternatives** when problems occur
- 📊 **Generating analytics** for transport planners to improve infrastructure

**Think of it as:** Google Maps Transit + Uber-like real-time tracking + City planning analytics—all in one platform.

---

## 🚨 The Problem We Solve

### Current Urban Commuting Pain Points:

**1. Fragmented Planning** 
- Use train app for schedule
- Use metro app for connections  
- Use bus app for last mile
- Manually piece it together
- **Result:** Confusion and wasted time

**2. Transfer Chaos**
- Unknown walking distances
- Unclear platform information
- Missed connections
- **Result:** Stress and delays

**3. Late Disruption Discovery**
- Learn about delays after boarding
- No alternative suggestions
- Manual replanning required
- **Result:** Late arrivals, frustration

**4. No Data for Planners**
- Infrastructure decisions lack data
- Reactive rather than proactive
- **Result:** Inefficient systems

### ✅ Our Solution:

TransitFlow provides **ONE interface** that:
- Plans complete multi-modal journeys
- Gives real-time updates and alerts
- Suggests alternatives instantly
- Tracks data for better planning

---

## ✨ Key Features

### For Daily Commuters

#### 🗺️ Smart Journey Planning
```
What you get:
✓ Multiple route options combining ALL transport modes
✓ Exact costs, times, and transfer details
✓ Reliability scores for each route
✓ Choose fastest OR cheapest
✓ Avoid specific modes (e.g., skip buses)

Example:
Bhayandar → Churchgate
├─ Walk 3 min to station
├─ Train 35 min (₹15)
├─ Transfer walk 5 min
├─ Metro 25 min (₹10)
└─ Walk 4 min to destination
Total: 72 min, ₹25, 2 transfers
```

#### ⚡ Real-Time Tracking
```
Updates every 30 seconds:
✓ Current vehicle position
✓ Crowd levels (low/medium/high)
✓ Platform delays
✓ Next segment reminders
✓ Transfer alerts
```

#### 🔄 Disruption Management
```
When delays happen:
1. Instant alert on your phone
2. Impact shown (e.g., "+15 min delay")
3. Alternative routes generated automatically
4. One-click to switch routes
```

### For Transport Planners

#### 📊 Analytics Dashboard
```
Real-time metrics:
• System Health: 78%
• On-Time Performance: 82%
• Active Disruptions: 3
• Daily Journeys: 127,453
```

#### 💡 Insights & Recommendations
```
Data-driven improvements:
• Popular routes identification
• Disruption hotspots
• Congestion patterns
• Infrastructure recommendations with ROI
```

---

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

```
Backend:   Node.js + Express + Socket.io
Frontend:  React 18 + Axios + Socket.io-client
Real-time: WebSocket (Socket.io)
Data:      In-memory (NodeCache) → Ready for PostgreSQL/MongoDB
Language:  JavaScript (ES6+)
Styling:   Custom CSS (CSS Variables, Dark Theme)
```

