## 🌍 Global Expansion & Accuracy Enhancements

This project is scaffolded to support global transit interoperability and smarter, more accurate travel experiences. Key planned and scaffolded features:

- **Open Transit Standards (GTFS + GTFS-RT)** 🔧
  - Adopt GTFS for static schedules and GTFS-RT for live updates to support city-to-city feeds without rewriting logic.
  - `backend/services/gtfsService.js` and `backend/services/gtfsRealtimeService.js` provide ingestion & RT polling scaffolds.

- **Multi-City Support** 🌆
  - Upload per-city GTFS packages, register GTFS-RT URLs, and select cities at runtime via frontend components.
  - `POST /api/feeds/upload/:cityId` and `POST /api/feeds/register-rt/:cityId` added.

- **Localization (Language & Currency)** 🌐
  - Auto-detect language/currency via location (country code heuristics) and expose translations.
  - `backend/services/localizationService.js` with example locales in `backend/locales/`.

- **AI / Accuracy Improvements** 🤖
  - Crowd prediction scaffolding (`backend/services/crowdPredictor.js`) uses historical analytics heuristics now; ML model training hooks are included.
  - Real-time disruption alerts are emitted via WebSockets and GTFS-RT vehicle/trip updates are proxied.

- **Carbon Tracking & Analytics** 🌱
  - `backend/services/carbonService.js` computes route-level CO₂ estimates.
  - `POST /api/carbon/estimate` to estimate CO₂ per route.

- **UX Enhancements (planned)** ⚡
  - Live map overlays, journey timelines, offline caching, personalization, and API-friendly endpoints are scaffolded on both frontend and backend for incremental implementation.

---

For full implementation details and next steps see `docs/FEATURE_ROADMAP.md`.

## 🔗 Recommended Free APIs

See `docs/EXTERNAL_APIS.md` for a curated list of free (or freemium) APIs useful for geocoding, traffic, weather, exchange rates, carbon intensity, and agency feeds. These services are referenced by new backend helpers in `backend/services/` and can be enabled via environment variables (see the `EXTERNAL_APIS.md` file for example `.env` entries).

